<section class="section-band" id="about-the-committee">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
    <h2>Better research starts by listening</h2>
    <p>Researchers do not always see the full experience of living with uveal melanoma. Patients can identify unanswered questions, overlooked concerns, and outcomes that matter in everyday life. The committee creates a direct way for those insights to guide our work.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="instrument-grid">
    <article class="instrument-card instrument-card-red">
      <h3>Start with patient priorities</h3>
      <p>Help researchers understand which challenges, questions, and uncertainties deserve greater attention.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="instrument-card instrument-card-orange">
      <h3>Shape meaningful research</h3>
      <p>Bring your perspective to research questions, plans, and outcomes so studies reflect patients' real needs.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="instrument-card instrument-card-green">
      <h3>Make findings more useful</h3>
      <p>Help us think about how research is communicated and how results can better serve patients and families.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-band section-band-alt" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
    <h2>Your perspective, throughout the process</h2>
    <p>The committee is a partnership. Researchers bring their methods and subject knowledge; patients bring lived experience. Together, we can set clearer priorities and develop research that is more relevant to the people it is meant to help.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="participation-flow">
    <article class="participation-step">
      <p class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">01</p>
      <div>
        <h3>Share what matters</h3>
        <p>Tell us about the questions, concerns, and gaps you believe research should address.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="participation-step">
      <p class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">02</p>
      <div>
        <h3>Help set priorities</h3>
        <p>Work with other patients and researchers to identify areas where research could make a meaningful difference.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="participation-step">
      <p class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">03</p>
      <div>
        <h3>Guide the research</h3>
        <p>Help translate shared priorities into research objectives and provide a patient perspective as the work develops.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-band" id="who-can-join">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Who can join</p>
    <h2>Lived experience is the qualification</h2>
    <p>We welcome people living in Canada who have been diagnosed with uveal melanoma, whether your diagnosis was recent or many years ago. You do not need a background in science, medicine, or research to take part.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="advisory-note">
    <p class="summary-label">A place for different perspectives</p>
    <p>Every experience of uveal melanoma is different. Bringing together people with a range of experiences can help us see what research needs to consider—and what it might otherwise miss.</p>
  </div>
</section>

